text:
I went here on a recommendation from others who stated that their produce was a great deal and of great quality.

I needed a couple of odds and ends and was nearby, so I gave it a shot.

This is just weird... now I know how Aldi works, I understand their business model and their intended goals, but its just not how I want to shop.

You can get some basics here, but you certainly can't get all of your grocery shopping done here; you'll definitely have to make a second trip to Giant Eagle or WalMart.

They have canned veggies;
A large cereal selection;
Basic dairy selection;
eggs;
some frozen meats;
some packaged frozen foods;
and, yes, they do have some produce--it did appear fresh, but it didn't blow my hair back!

You have to use a quarter to get a cart to shop with which is refunded to you when you return your cart--keeps costs low so they don't have to pay someone to retrieve carts from the lot.

I don't know, I can't see myself going back, which is a bummer because I went in here with an open mind and kind of enthusiastic, in hopes of finding a new shopping location.
